Stakeholders in Kisumu have urged greater promotion of investment in water. Kisumu Governor Anyang’ Nyong’o said there is great potential in the sector that remains underutilised, despite Kisumu being endowed with Lake Victoria. Nyong’o urged stakeholders to chip in to spur development. Read more : Five things Kenya can do to meet its energy needs He was speaking in Kisumu on Wednesday when he opened the County Water Investment Conference. Scientists, businesspeople, government agencies, national and international non-state actors attended the conference. The governor said some of the untapped opportunities, such as marine transport, hydropower generation and irrigation, need investment. Read more : AfDB gives Sh102m for Central Kenya’s hydropower Click here for more political news 